premise_source_doc_sentence: Dhruva  (  ध्रुव `` constant , immovable , fixed ''  )  is a devotee of Vishnu mentioned in the Vishnu Purana and the Bhagavata Purana .
The Sanskrit term dhruva nakshatra `` immovable star '' is used of the polar star in the Mahabharata , personified as son of Uttanapada and grandson of Manu , even though Polaris
at the likely period of the recension of the text of the Mahabharata was still several degrees away from the celestial pole .
Super Commando Dhruva , whose complete name is Dhruva Mehra , is additionally referred to as Captain Dhruva by the cadets of his Commando Force .
The first major recurring supporting character to be introduced in Dhruva series was his foster father I. G. Rajan Mehra in Dhruva 's debut title itself .
Dhruva also has a well known rogues gallery full of an assortment of supervillains including Grand Master Robo , Chandakaal and Mahamanav .
At times , Dhruva has appeared alongside other superheroes of Raj comics universe in multi-hero crossovers .
The deity is believed to imbibe the essence of the Dhruva Bera as well as grant devotees ' wishes .
